0 \le \phi \le f
\int f - \phi \, d\mu < \frac{\epsilon}{2}.
\phi = \sum_{k=1}^n c_k \chi_{C_k}.
 \int_A \phi \, d\mu = \sum_k c_k \mu(A \cap C_k) \le \mu(A) \sum_{k=1}^n c_k
\delta = \frac{\epsilon}{2 \sum _{k=1}^n c_k}
\mu(A) < \delta \implies \int_A f \, d\mu  \le \int (f-\phi) \, d\mu  + \int_A \phi \, d\mu< \epsilon.
